snippet.title: Computex 2013
snippet.description: All the news from Computex 2013, the largest IT tradeshow in Asia.

snippet.title: TDK Life on Record A33 Wireless Weatherproof Speaker
snippet.description: While the TDK Life on Record A33 Wireless Weatherproof Speaker has a few small shortcomings, it delivers very good sound for its size and price and is well suited to both indoor and outdoor use with a sturdy, splashproof design.

snippet.title: 2014 Jaguar XJL Portfolio AWD
snippet.description: The smooth and quiet 2014 Jaguar XJL makes driver and passenger comfort its top priority. This luxury sedan and its tech may be aging, but they're doing so gracefully.

snippet.title: Aboard the world's largest model train collection
snippet.description: Road Trip 2011: Every year more than a million people visit Miniatur Wunderland, featuring 900 trains, eight miles of track, an airport, and dioramas from several countries. CNET gets a backstage look.

snippet.title: World's largest TV, 'Big Hoss,' is as long as a jet
snippet.description: "Big Hoss," soon to be confirmed as the largest TV in the world by the Guinness Book of World Records, has been switched on in Texas to the delight of thousands of "Duck Dynasty"-loving racing fans.

snippet.title: How to give an albino alligator a CT scan
snippet.description: Getting an alligator to sit still for a CT scan is a challenge, especially when you know he can't be sedated.

snippet.title: Wolfgang Puck Pressure Oven
snippet.description: Packing the benefits of pressure cooking into a countertop oven is a pretty clever idea. Chef Puck's oven isn't perfect, and at $249 it isn't for everyone, but crafty home cooks will nonetheless appreciate its performance.

snippet.title: Samsung shipped record 320M smartphones in 2013
snippet.description: South Korean electronics giant grabs 32 percent market share during a year that saw an overall record of 990 million smartphone shipments, according to Strategy Analytics.

snippet.title: Awesome fire-breathing dragon is world's largest walking robot
snippet.description: At 30 feet tall and 51 feet long, Tradinno is a gargantuan mechatronic beast you don't want to mess with.

snippet.title: Record dinosaur tail unearthed in Mexico
snippet.description: Paleontologists in the northern Mexican state of Coahuila reveal a 16-foot dinosaur tail with 50 connected vertebrae intact.
